fication:</span>&nbsp;Bachelor</li><li><span class=\"font--weight-500\">Experience Level:</span>&nbsp;Mid level</li><li><span class=\"font--weight-500\">Experience Length:</span>&nbsp;3 years</li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"customer-card card--compact\" style=\"position: relative; display: inline-flex; -webkit-box-orient: vertical; -webkit-box-direction: normal; flex-direction: column; width: 870px; margin: 0px 0px 1px; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.07) 0px 2px 2px 0px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1) 0px 3px 1px -2px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06) 0px 1px 5px 0px; color: rgb(78, 85, 89); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><div class=\"customer-card__content-segment padding-top--20\" style=\"padding: 10px 0px; position: relative; display: inline-flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; width: 870px; -webkit-box-orient: vertical; -webkit-box-direction: normal; flex-direction: column;\"><div class=\"customer-card--row padding-lr-30 padding-lr--20-under-lg\" style=\"padding: 0px 20px; position: relative; display: inline-flex; -webkit-box-orient: horizontal; -webkit-box-direction: normal; flex-direction: row; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; width: 870px; -webkit-box-pack: justify; justify-content: space-between; min-height: 40px;\"><div class=\"job__details__user-edit wrapper--inline-block float--left\" style=\"float: left; display: inline-block; width: 810px; position: relative;\"><h3 class=\"font-size-18 margin-top--0 margin-bottom--15\" style=\"color: rgb(78, 85, 89); font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 15px;\">Job Description</h3><div class=\"job__details__user-edit description-content__content\" style=\"position: relative; display: inline-block; float: left; width: 810px;\"><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1;\">Reports to:</span>&nbsp;Chief Executive Officer<br></p><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">The primary objectives of the Finance &amp; Administration Officer role are:<br></p><ul style=\"margin: 15px 0px;\"><li>To ensure that all financial and office management including statutory compliance systems are in place and adhered to.</li><li>To ensure that the appropriate financial and administrative infrastructure is in place to support the provision of the organization’s services to its staff, clients, business partners and&nbsp; the general public including strategic financial planning.</li></ul><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\"><br></p><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">Key Responsibilities:</p><ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\"><li>To maintain an efficient working office environment, including management of office accommodation, equipment and supplies, office health and safety, including IT and online support.</li><li>To develop, implement and embed efficient office processes and procedures to meet legislation, data protection requirements and best business practice.</li><li>To provide general staff administration and ensure personal adherence to the organization’s HR Manual and oversee adherence of staff to the same.</li><li>To ensure that creditor, debtor and debt management processes maximize organizational financial outcomes.</li><li>To ensure effective management of the organization’s cash-flow including cash-flow budgeting and forecasting.</li><li>To produce and provide monthly management accounts to the CEO and relevant budget reports.</li><li>To support the CEO in production and presentation of Finance reports for Board meetings.</li><li>To maintain an efficient, timely and compliant payroll function.</li><li>To ensure compliance management including statutory compliance and taxation (annual accounts and audit, NHIF, NSSF, PAYE, VAT, etc.).</li><li>To work with the management team to maintain the company’s and individual project budgets.</li><li>To develop and maintain policies relevant to the organization’s financial management.</li><li>To manage the register of contracts, assets and security of assets.</li><li>To manage insurance and loan/borrowing arrangements.</li><li>To provide strategic financial planning of the organization in conjunction with the CEO and the Finance &amp; Planning Committee.</li><li>To work with the management team and the Finance &amp; Planning Committee to develop and implement budgetary system improvements.</li><li>To perform any other duties as directed by the CEO.</li></ol><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\"><br></p><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">Job Requirements:</p><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">i. Education and Training:</p><ul style=\"margin: 15px 0px;\"><li>A Degree in Business Management, Finance or equivalent and CPA (K) qualification.</li></ul><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">ii. Job Experience:</p><ul style=\"margin: 15px 0px;\"><li>At least three (3) years’ experience in key facets of financial management such as, among others, developing and maintaining budgets and cash-flows, overseeing creditors and debtors, statutory compliance.</li></ul><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">iii. Other Competencies:</p><ul style=\"margin: 15px 0px;\"><li>Proficiency in accounting packages</li><li>Excellent IT skills with strong knowledge of Excel and Word</li><li>Strong planning and organizational skills</li><li>Excellent interpersonal, motivational, written and oral communication skills</li><li>Strong analytical and decision-making skills</li><li>Strong stakeholder service focus</li><li>Ability to work as a member of a team, to motivate, provide direction and influence</li><li>Good negotiation skills</li><li>Ability to work confidentially, with tact and discretion</li></ul><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\"><br></p><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">Key Contacts:</p><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">Internal</p><ul style=\"margin: 15px 0px;\"><li>Chief Executive Officer</li><li>Finance &amp; Planning Committee</li><li>Projects Management Committee</li><li>All Staff</li></ul><p style=\"word-break: normal; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px !important;\">External</p><ul style=\"margin: 15px 0px;\"><li>Clients</li><li>Creditors &amp; Debtors</li><li>Service Providers</li><li>Auditors</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div>                                                                            ', 'documents/5e667e8e66392_1583775374.pdf', '09-Mar-2020', '2020-03-14', 1, 'full time', 9);

